      "source": [
        "### Chain of Thought\n",
        "\n",
        "You'll notice that, by default, the model uses Chain of Thought to answer difficult questions - but it can still benefit from a Chain of Thought Prompt to increase the reliability of the response!\n",
        "\n",
        "> This pattern is leveraged even more by advanced reasoning models like [`o3` and `o4-mini`](https://openai.com/index/introducing-o3-and-o4-mini/)!"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 14,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 151
        },
        "id": "cwW0IgbfeTwP",
        "outputId": "3317783b-6b23-4e38-df48-555e1a3c9fac"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": [
              "Let's analyze both options carefully:\n",
              "\n",
              "**Option 1: Fly + Bus**\n",
              "- Flying takes 3 hours.\n",
              "- Then taking a bus takes 2 hours.\n",
              "- Total travel time: 3 + 2 = **5 hours**.\n",
              "\n",
              "**Option 2: Teleporter + Bus**\n",
              "- Teleporter is instantaneous: 0 hours.\n",
              "- Bus takes 1 hour.\n",
              "- Total travel time: 0 + 1 = **1 hour**.\n",
              "\n",
              "**Current time:** 1PM local time.\n",
              "\n",
              "**Goal:** Get home **before 7PM EDT**.\n",
              "\n",
              "Assuming the local time is *not* EDT but a different timezone, we need to clarify the time difference. Since Billy is in San Francisco (Pacific Time Zone), and the deadline is in EDT, we need to account for the timezone difference:\n",
              "\n",
              "- Pacific Time (PT) is 3 hours behind Eastern Time (ET).  \n",
              "  - When it's 1PM PT, it's 4PM ET.\n",
              "\n",
